{\rtf1\ansi \deff0{\fonttbl{\f8\fswiss Arial;}}\margl720\margr2160\pgnstart216\sectd\pgnrestart\pgnstarts216\footery1080{\header \pard\plain\ql MYARC ADVANCED BASIC\par }{\footer \pard\plain\ql \chpgn     VERSION 4.0  DDI SOFTWARE  \par }\pard \plain\f8\fs20 TCOLOR --Subprogram\tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab          TCOLOR\par \par \par \par \par Format\par CALL TCOLOR(foreground-color,background color)\par \par Cross Reference\par PALETTE\par \par Description\par The TCOLOR subprogram enables you to change the foreground-color and background-color of text characters.\par \par In bit map modes, the color set for a given portion of text remains even when subsequent text is changed.\par \par In text modes, when colors are changed, all text is changed at the same time.\par \par Color numbers range from 1 to the number of colors available to the mode(4,16,256).  See PALETTE\par \par Example\par \par 100 CALL TCOLOR(16,5)\par This sets the foreground-color to white and the background-color to dark blue. \par This is the default color when you enter MYARC Advanced BASIC.\par }
